The issue occurs in the varargs handling. When `invocation.getMethod().isVarArgs()` is true, the code assumes that all elements in the raw arguments after the non-vararg positions constitute the varargs array. However, for mixed varargs (non-vararg parameters followed by varargs), the vararg elements are stored as an array in the last position of the raw arguments, not as individual elements.

